# Build context exclusions for the backend image.
#
# Anything listed here is NOT sent to the docker daemon. Keeping the build
# context lean speeds up `docker build` and prevents host-side state (local
# secrets, IDE configs, OS junk) from leaking into image layers.

# Dependencies — reinstalled deterministically inside the builder stage from
# `package.json` + `yarn.lock`. Copying the host's tree would slow the build
# AND risk mixing host-architecture binaries (e.g. macOS) into a Linux image.
node_modules/

# Compiled output — produced inside the builder stage. Copying the host's
# `dist/` would mask stale build artifacts behind a fresh image.
dist/

# Test coverage reports — runtime artefact, never needed at build time.
coverage/

# Runtime secrets — `.env` is mode 600 on the host and must never enter an
# image layer. Backups (`.env.bak.*`) are equally sensitive.
.env
.env.*
.env.bak.*

# Local file-storage volume — production runtime data, not source.
uploads/

# Log files — host-side debug noise.
logs/
*.log

# VCS metadata — leaks history (and any unredacted secrets) into layers.
.git/

# Editor / IDE / OS scratch.
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store

# Test sources — production images do not run tests. The Jest suite stays
# on the host (and CI), not inside the runtime image.
test/

# Local Prisma dev SQLite database (only present when developers switch the
# datasource to sqlite for offline work). Never wanted in a production image.
prisma/migrations/dev.db*

# Operator-facing docs — image runs without them.
README.md
